Font_CharBBox  (&4008E)
#Parent Font_
=>	R0 =	font handle
	R1 =	character
	R2 =	<flags=>font_paintflags> (only bit 4 matters)

<=	R1 =	min x incl
	R2 =	min y incl
	R3 =	max x excl
	R4 =	max y excl

This SWI returns the bounding box for the given character of the given font. The bounding box is the smallest box neccessary to cover the character.
#Line
See <PRM 3, page 446=>PRM-3:446>.
